sub_title: Math analyst II at GLI Europe B.V.
summary:
Aerospace Engineering graduate living in the Netherlands with 2 years of experience in the regulatory and certification market, with diverse skills in and a passion for programming and data analysis. I also have a strong interest in machine learning, its principles and applications.
I thrive in an international environment and pursue any opportunity to learn new skills and develop myself. This, coupled with my programming and analysis skills and attention to detail, allows me to perform at my best in a market where staying constantly updated to simulate and deliver accurate results is crucial.
Outside of work, I love reading the classics of world literature and doing sports. I also have a penchant for cooking.
